<p>I have the a String where one tag contains special character. i want to convert the only the data which have special characters to xml format. example one tag contains <code>&lt;text&gt;ab&amp;!ab&lt;/text&gt;</code> should be converted to <code>&lt;text&gt;ab&amp;amp;&lt;/text&gt;</code></p>  <p>I have tried the below code but how can i handle if a tag data contains &lt; or >  example <code>&lt;text&gt;ab&amp;&lt;!ab&lt;/text&gt;</code>  code:- string xml= "ab&amp;!'ab"; string result = Regex.Replace(xml,"&amp;(?!(amp|quot|lt|gt);)","&amp;"); string result1 = Regex.Replace(result, "'(?!(amp|quot|lt|gt);)", "&apos;");</p>